gobblin.config.client.api

Enum VersionStabilityPolicy

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<VersionStabilityPolicy>
      • gobblin.config.client.api.VersionStabilityPolicy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<VersionStabilityPolicy>

    @Alpha
public enum VersionStabilityPolicy
extends Enum<VersionStabilityPolicy>
    This policy specifies the behavior expected by the client application when making repeated calls to fetch the configuration object for the same config key and version. This interface is closely associated with the ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning API.

    The semantic of each policy is documented with each constant.

    Here is the table that summarizes the expected client library behavior depending on the VersionStabilityPolicy and ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning support from a store.

    VersionStabilityPolicy/ConfigStoreWithStableVersioning No Yes
    CROSS_JVM_STABILITY ERROR WeakCache
    STRONG_LOCAL_STABILITY StrongCache WeakCache
    WEAK_LOCAL_STABILITY WeakCache WeakCache
    READ_FRESHEST NoCache WeakCache
    • ERROR means that the client library should throw an exception because the requested VersionStabilityPolicy cannot be supported
    • WeakCache means that the client library may cache in memory configs that have been already read for performance reasons and if memory allows it.
    • StrongCache means that the client library should always cache in memory the read configs to guarantee the requested VersionStabilityPolicy
    • NoCache means that the client library should never cache the read configs.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CROSS_JVM_STABILITY
      Reading the same config key and version from different JVMs must return the same result.
      READ_FRESHEST
      The application needs to read the most recent config if the underlying store does not support stable versioning.
      STRONG_LOCAL_STABILITY
      Reading the same config key and version from the same JVMs must return the same result.
      WEAK_LOCAL_STABILITY
      The application does not depend on getting the same config for the same key and version but the client library may use caching to improve performance.
